From cdff1af62181b58c0326f4a441eea656391425ac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 11:12:44 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] lib/math: translate lcm, int_log, int_pow, int_sqrt to Rust
 (linux-rs batch 2)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four more TUs, same discipline as gcd (faithful, no optimisation):
- int_sqrt: shift-and-subtract, __fls -> leading_zeros; int_sqrt64 not
  translated (BITS_PER_LONG==64 here, not compiled)
- int_log: LGPL-2.1-or-later preserved; logtable const; C integer
  promotion in the interpolation reproduced exactly; WARN_ON(1) ->
  kernel::warn_on! (real taint semantics); unlikely() hint dropped
- int_pow: C wrapping multiplication -> wrapping_mul
- lcm: first Rust->Rust cross-TU call via the C ABI (bindings::gcd);
  GNU ?: elvis translated explicitly

Validated on qemu-system-riscv64 -M virt boot: 58/58 KUnit vectors
across math-gcd (11), math-int_log (17, incl. WARN paths), math-int_pow
(9), math-int_sqrt (21). EXPORT_SYMBOL (non-GPL) on int_sqrt/intlog2/
intlog10 becomes EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL under #[export] — reviewed, accepted
for this corpus (CONFIG_MODULES=n), tracked in rule 0001.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
